      • isUniqueInClass

        public boolean isUniqueInClass(MetafieldId inUniqueField,
                               boolean inIsScopingEnabled)
        Check if value for a field is unique amongst all instances of this class. Intended to be called from validate() methods, is safe during interception as it creates its own Hibernate session to do the test so as to not corrupt the current open session.
        Parameters:
        inUniqueField - unique field to validate
        inIsScopingEnabled - indicates if scoping should be considered during validation or not. Carina doesn't have scoping, but applications do. For instance N4 uses operator/facility scoping rules and with this parameter = false, domain query that validates uniqueness will not be enhanced with scoping rules.
        Returns:
        true if no other instance has the same value for the field "inUniqueField"

        public void preDelete()
        Description copied from interface: IEntityLifeCycle
        Called before delete is called. However this is only guaranteed to be called because HibernateApi.delete was invoked. Entities deleted by cascades will not be handled here. Logic involving children deleted by cascade should currently be put on the parent.
